# Notion Time Tracker — Project Conventions

Read `AI_PROJECT_GUIDE.md` at the project root for full architecture, API reference, and data flow documentation.

## Stack

- **Backend**: Node.js + Express 5, SQLite, @notionhq/client
- **Frontend**: React 19, Vite 6, Tailwind CSS 4, React Router 7, Axios
- **Deployment**: Docker Compose (nginx fronts the frontend in prod)

## Key Conventions

- Timezone is **Pacific/Auckland** (NZ). All date logic must account for this.
- Currency is **NZD** with **15% GST**. Billing rounds time up to 0.25h increments.
- Notion sync is manual (`POST /api/sync/notion`). Never add auto-sync without discussion.
- The app is single-user with no auth layer.
- SQLite migrations use `ALTER TABLE ... ADD COLUMN` with silent no-op in `database.js`.
- Frontend proxies `/api` to the backend (Vite in dev, nginx in prod).

## Sync Behaviour

- Sync fetches only active tasks (Status = "To Do" or "Doing") from Notion.
- Tasks no longer returned by Notion are marked "Done" locally so they leave the Quick Start list.
- Notion property names are **exact-match** (e.g. "Task Name", "Project Link", "Deadline").

## Timeline Component

`TimelineView.jsx` is the most complex component. After changes, update the version log:

```js
console.log("🕒 TimelineView last updated @ <date> — <description>");
```

Test drag, resize, create, and delete interactions after any timeline edit.
